[[!meta title="Energy Drink — Ghost Energy Iced Tea Lemonade"]]
[[!tag Review Energy_Drink]]

Ghost's Iced Tea Lemonade flavor was released on May 5 2025. Recently Ghost has
experimented with flavors outside of their typical brand partnerships, like the
Peaches flavor released earlier this year. The can a pretty pastel blue with
yellow accents.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreiblq752hrga63qrpvqdusjudrgplgwtceocov3t25zhn5yrdsctmi" size=medium]]
</figure>

First off it's carbonated. Why is a drink called "iced tea lemonade" bubbly?
This is extremely upsetting and disturbing. Each drink from the can is a deluge
of bubbles masking the actual flavor.

Putting the bubbles aside (which is hard to do), it doesn't taste like iced tea
nor lemonade. The thing in itself, iced tea and lemonade, is an [[!wikipedia
Arnold_Palmer_(drink)]], but Ghost's interpretation of it is so far from this
idea it's confusing. The taste is artificially sour up-front and musky on the
finish, like a plum that's way too ripe. It's not bitter but the taste is
neither accurate, refreshing nor very pleasant. This is either the worst Ghost
I've had or just barely on-par with [[Ghost_Energy_x_Faze_Clan_Faze_Pop]].
